cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.HC, cs.AI, cs.NE

The paper proposes a few-shot learning method for human activity recognition using wearable sensors. This involves using a deep learning model for feature extraction and classification, which suggests the paper could fall under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the use of wearable sensors implies a focus on computer vision (cs.CV) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also involves knowledge transfer and parameter transfer, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE).
